All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Add
The Add class represents a command to add a person to the collection.
AddIfMax
The AddIfMax class represents a command to add a person to the collection if it is the maximum.
Clear
The Clear class represents a command to clear the collection.
Command
The Command interface represents a command that can be executed with arguments.
CommandInvoker
The CommandInvoker class manages the execution of commands and maintains command history.
Coordinates
The Coordinates class represents a pair of coordinates.
CoordinatesMaker
The CoordinatesMaker class provides a method to create coordinates based on user input.
Country
The Country enum represents a set of countries.
CountryMaker
The CountryMaker class provides a method to select a country based on user input.
ExecuteScript
The ExecuteScript class represents a command to execute a script from a file.
Exit
The Exit class represents a command to exit the program.
EyeColor
The EyeColor enum represents a set of eye colors.
EyeColorMaker
The EyeColorMaker class provides a method to select an eye color based on user input.
FilterGTN
The FilterGTN class represents a command to filter persons by nationality.
HairColor
The HairColor enum represents a set of hair colors.
HairColorMaker
The HairColorMaker class provides a method to select a hair color based on user input.
Help
The Help class represents a command to display help information about available commands.
History
The History class represents a command to display the command history.
IdStorage
The IdStorage class manages the generation of unique IDs.
Info
The Info class represents a command to display information about the collection.
LoadCollection
The LoadCollection class represents a command to load a collection of Person objects from a JSON file.
Location
The Location class represents a geographical location with coordinates and a name.
LocationMaker
The LocationMaker class provides a method to create a location object based on user input.
Main
The Main class contains the main method to start the program.
Person
The Person class represents a person with various attributes.
PersonMaker
The PersonMaker class provides a method to create a Person object with specified attributes.
PersonManager
The PersonManager class manages a collection of Person objects.
PrintDesc
The PrintDesc class represents a command to print the elements of the collection in descending order.
RemoveAllByHeight
The RemoveAllByHeight class represents a command to remove all elements from the collection with the specified height.
RemoveById
The RemoveById class represents a command to remove an element from the collection by its id.
RemoveLower
The RemoveLower class represents a command to remove all elements from the collection lower than the specified one.
Save
The Save class represents a command to save the collection to a file in JSON format.
Show
The Show class represents a command to display all elements of the collection.
UpdateId
The UpdateId class represents a command to update an element in the collection by its id.
